title: Budget stopgap sets up Congress for bigger fight PBS NewsHour
text: Congress passed a bill to extend funding until December, hours before the deadline for a possible government shutdown. But the sharply divided vote in the House only seems to set up a potentially bigger fight later on. Political director Lisa Desjardins talks with Judy Woodruff from Capitol Hill.
